   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">2.1.1b Number of HHs/persons benefiting from new or additional social assistance measures provided by governments to respond to COVID-19 with JP support (disaggregated by age, sex)
2.1.1.c Number of social service workforce professionals/allied professionals who benefitted from capacity development activities (disaggregated by age and sex)
2.1.1.d MoLSA procedures for collecting and analyzing COVID-19 related and LNOB (disaggregated by age, sex, vulnerability, location) data are developed.
2.2.1 b Number of scoring mechanisms developed to improve access to finance for microbusinesses and unregistered entrepreneurs. 
2.2.1.cNumber of forecasting scenariosdeveloped in agricultural sector for improved COVID-19 response planning and targeting (beneficiariesdisaggregated by age and sex)</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">2.1.1b: 0
2.1.1c: 0
2.21.1d- Few procedures in place, but data not synchronized and not comparable
2.2.1b:0
2.2.1.c:0</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Procedures in place, allowing fordisaggregated data analysis, comparability and forecasting
Rapid service targeting and planning, using alternative and innovative data collection and visualisation tools.
Barriers for the effective roll-out of the Government support package to MSMEs removed
3 forecasting scenarios</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Data collection and analytics support to MoSLA
- Support to the Health and Labour Inspection (hard investment)
 New financial scoring mechanism designed in collaboration with the Minisiry of Economy
Three scenarios modelled in the agriculture sector for effective planning and targeting of COVID-19 support/recovery activities
-Data collected and analysed
-Foresign modellingundertaken and results presented to the Ministry of Economy</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conducting Rapid Assessment and Mapping of Data and Process Gaps
Development of the Rapid needs assessment platform
Development of the online EmployeeProtect.am platform, as well as mobile IOS and Android versions
UNDP Mobile Testing Service Pilot
Social taxi and Social assistant pilot
New financial scoring mechanism designed and implemented in collaboration with the Minisitry of Economy</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Initial mapping was implemented for Conducting Rapid Assessment and Mapping of Data and Process Gaps, the next step for detailed assessment is still in process, as it was on hold for quite some time because of the conflict situation. 
Support of Rapid needs assessment platform developed together with UNICEF and Norq information analytical center is in progress.
In the framework of the Grant Agreement, the EmployeeProtect.am platform, which is aimed at reporting and protecting the employees&#x2019; rights, has already been developed together with the Health and Labor inspection. 
Business plan for Social taxi and Social assistant has been sent to MoLSA, waiting for feedback. Further discussions have been impeded due to current situation.
UNDP Mobile Testing Service Pilot:1) needs assessment and the co-design of the mobile testing service is completed. 2) procurement of the equipment for the pilot is in process; 3) the management system for the new service is in process (tablets are procured, Wi-Fi internet connection as well as the application development is in process), 4) capacity needs of the nurses to deliver the new service are identified and the training preparation in the process and 5) the roadmap for the new service pilot is in development process. 
Project Concept, data provision system and Implementing Partner selection criteria included in Proposal (RFP) are agreed with ACRA credit bureau and the Ministry of Economy.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
